channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: Edge2Node: Reducing Edge Prediction to Node Classification
item.description: A common approach for edge prediction is to first obtain the embeddings of two nodes, and then a predefined scoring function is used to predict the existence of an edge between the two nodes.

item.title: TabRepo: A Large Scale Repository of Tabular Model Evaluations and its AutoML Applications
item.description: TabRepo contains the predictions and metrics of 1206 models evaluated on 200 regression and classification datasets.

item.title: CogVLM: Visual Expert for Pretrained Language Models
item.description: We introduce CogVLM, a powerful open-source visual language foundation model.

item.title: OVIR-3D: Open-Vocabulary 3D Instance Retrieval Without Training on 3D Data
item.description: This work presents OVIR-3D, a straightforward yet effective method for open-vocabulary 3D object instance retrieval without using any 3D data for training.

item.title: QualEval: Qualitative Evaluation for Model Improvement
item.description: In this work, we address the shortcomings of quantitative metrics by proposing QualEval, which augments quantitative scalar metrics with automated qualitative evaluation as a vehicle for model improvement.

item.title: FocusTune: Tuning Visual Localization through Focus-Guided Sampling
item.description: We propose FocusTune, a focus-guided sampling technique to improve the performance of visual localization algorithms.

item.title: LitSumm: Large language models for literature summarisation of non-coding RNAs
item.description: Availability: Code used to produce these summaries can be found here: https://github. com/RNAcentral/litscan-summarization and the dataset of contexts and summaries can be found here: https://huggingface. co/datasets/RNAcentral/litsumm-v1.

item.title: Estimating treatment effects from single-arm trials via latent-variable modeling
item.description: Compared to previous methods, our results show improved performance both for direct treatment effect estimation as well as for effect estimation via patient matching.

item.title: A survey and classification of face alignment methods based on face models
item.description: Face alignment is the process of fitting the landmarks in a face model to the respective ground truth positions in an input image containing a face.

item.title: Persistent homology for high-dimensional data based on spectral methods
item.description: As a remedy, we find that spectral distances on the $k$-nearest-neighbor graph of the data, such as diffusion distance and effective resistance, allow persistent homology to detect the correct topology even in the presence of high-dimensional noise.

item.title: Convergence Analysis of Sequential Federated Learning on Heterogeneous Data
item.description: There are two categories of methods in Federated Learning (FL) for joint training across multiple clients: i) parallel FL (PFL), where clients train models in a parallel manner; and ii) sequential FL (SFL), where clients train models in a sequential manner.

item.title: Mini Minds: Exploring Bebeshka and Zlata Baby Models
item.description: In this paper, we describe the University of Lyon 2 submission to the Strict-Small track of the BabyLM competition.

item.title: Validity problems in clinical machine learning by indirect data labeling using consensus definitions
item.description: We demonstrate a validity problem of machine learning in the vital application area of disease diagnosis in medicine.

item.title: The Pursuit of Human Labeling: A New Perspective on Unsupervised Learning
item.description: Despite its simplicity, HUME outperforms a supervised linear classifier on top of self-supervised representations on the STL-10 dataset by a large margin and achieves comparable performance on the CIFAR-10 dataset.

item.title: Unraveling Downstream Gender Bias from Large Language Models: A Study on AI Educational Writing Assistance
item.description: Our results demonstrate that there is no significant difference in gender bias between the resulting peer reviews of groups with and without LLM suggestions.

item.title: Variational Weighting for Kernel Density Ratios
item.description: Kernel density estimation (KDE) is integral to a range of generative and discriminative tasks in machine learning.

item.title: FATE: Feature-Agnostic Transformer-based Encoder for learning generalized embedding spaces in flow cytometry data
item.description: This limitation becomes particularly relevant in scenarios where the attributes captured during data acquisition vary across different samples.

item.title: PhoGPT: Generative Pre-training for Vietnamese
item.description: We open-source a state-of-the-art 7. 5B-parameter generative model series named PhoGPT for Vietnamese, which includes the base pre-trained monolingual model PhoGPT-7B5 and its instruction-following variant, PhoGPT-7B5-Instruct.

item.title: GLEN: Generative Retrieval via Lexical Index Learning
item.description: For training, GLEN effectively exploits a dynamic lexical identifier using a two-phase index learning strategy, enabling it to learn meaningful lexical identifiers and relevance signals between queries and documents.

item.title: Dynamic Neural Fields for Learning Atlases of 4D Fetal MRI Time-series
item.description: We apply our method to learning subject-specific atlases and motion stabilization of dynamic BOLD MRI time-series of fetuses in utero.

item.title: Architectural Sweet Spots for Modeling Human Label Variation by the Example of Argument Quality: It's Best to Relate Perspectives!
item.description: To best represent the interplay of individual and shared perspectives, we consider a continuum of approaches ranging from models that fully aggregate perspectives into a majority label to "share nothing"-architectures in which each annotator is considered in isolation from all other annotators.

item.title: Language Models are Super Mario: Absorbing Abilities from Homologous Models as a Free Lunch
item.description: Based on this observation, we further sparsify delta parameters of multiple SFT homologous models with DARE and subsequently merge them into a single model by parameter averaging.

item.title: A universal framework for accurate and efficient geometric deep learning of molecular systems
item.description: Molecular sciences address a wide range of problems involving molecules of different types and sizes and their complexes.

item.title: BanLemma: A Word Formation Dependent Rule and Dictionary Based Bangla Lemmatizer
item.description: Lemmatization holds significance in both natural language processing (NLP) and linguistics, as it effectively decreases data density and aids in comprehending contextual meaning.

item.title: Nonparametric modeling of the composite effect of multiple nutrients on blood glucose dynamics
item.description: By differentiating treatment components, incorporating their dosages, and sharing statistical information across patients via a hierarchical multi-output Gaussian process, our method improves prediction accuracy over existing approaches, and allows us to interpret the different effects of carbohydrates and fat on the overall glucose response.

item.title: Rethinking Evaluation Metrics of Open-Vocabulary Segmentaion
item.description: We benchmarked the proposed evaluation metrics on 12 open-vocabulary methods of three segmentation tasks.

item.title: Pseudo-Labeling for Domain-Agnostic Bangla Automatic Speech Recognition
item.description: Our results demonstrate the efficacy of the model trained on psuedo-label data for the designed test-set along with publicly-available Bangla datasets.

item.title: GLaMM: Pixel Grounding Large Multimodal Model
item.description: In this work, we present Grounding LMM (GLaMM), the first model that can generate natural language responses seamlessly intertwined with corresponding object segmentation masks.

item.title: Weight-Sharing Regularization
item.description: Weight-sharing is ubiquitous in deep learning.

item.title: MultiSPANS: A Multi-range Spatial-Temporal Transformer Network for Traffic Forecast via Structural Entropy Optimization
item.description: Based on this, we propose a relative structural entropy-based position encoding and a multi-head attention masking scheme based on multi-layer encoding trees.

item.title: Efficient, Self-Supervised Human Pose Estimation with Inductive Prior Tuning
item.description: We (1) analyze the relationship between reconstruction quality and pose estimation accuracy, (2) develop a model pipeline that outperforms the baseline which inspired our work, using less than one-third the amount of training data, and (3) offer a new metric suitable for self-supervised settings that measures the consistency of predicted body part length proportions.

item.title: Kinematic-aware Prompting for Generalizable Articulated Object Manipulation with LLMs
item.description: Generalizable articulated object manipulation is essential for home-assistant robots.

item.title: Holistic Analysis of Hallucination in GPT-4V(ision): Bias and Interference Challenges
item.description: To bridge this gap, we introduce a new benchmark, namely, the Bias and Interference Challenges in Visual Language Models (Bingo).

item.title: Tailoring Self-Rationalizers with Multi-Reward Distillation
item.description: Results on five difficult question-answering datasets StrategyQA, QuaRel, OpenBookQA, NumerSense and QASC show that not only does MaRio improve task accuracy, but it also improves the self-rationalization quality of small LMs across the aforementioned axes better than a supervised fine-tuning (SFT) baseline.

item.title: Stable Linear Subspace Identification: A Machine Learning Approach
item.description: Machine Learning (ML) and linear System Identification (SI) have been historically developed independently.

item.title: Unified Multi-modal Unsupervised Representation Learning for Skeleton-based Action Understanding
item.description: In this manner, our framework is able to learn the unified representations of uni-modal or multi-modal skeleton input, which is flexible to different kinds of modality input for robust action understanding in practical cases.

item.title: Human as Points: Explicit Point-based 3D Human Reconstruction from Single-view RGB Images
item.description: The latest trends in the research field of single-view human reconstruction devote to learning deep implicit functions constrained by explicit body shape priors.

item.title: LCPR: A Multi-Scale Attention-Based LiDAR-Camera Fusion Network for Place Recognition
item.description: However, most existing multimodal place recognition methods only use limited field-of-view camera images, which leads to an imbalance between features from different modalities and limits the effectiveness of sensor fusion.

item.title: Instructed Language Models with Retrievers Are Powerful Entity Linkers
item.description: Generative approaches powered by large language models (LLMs) have demonstrated emergent abilities in tasks that require complex reasoning abilities.

item.title: Practical considerations for variable screening in the Super Learner
item.description: However, the performance of a Super Learner using the lasso for dimension reduction has not been fully explored in cases where the lasso is known to perform poorly.

item.title: Deep Image Semantic Communication Model for Artificial Intelligent Internet of Things
item.description: Particularly, at the transmitter side, a high-precision image semantic segmentation algorithm is proposed to extract the semantic information of the image to achieve significant compression of the image data.

item.title: APGL4SR: A Generic Framework with Adaptive and Personalized Global Collaborative Information in Sequential Recommendation
item.description: To this end, we propose a graph-driven framework, named Adaptive and Personalized Graph Learning for Sequential Recommendation (APGL4SR), that incorporates adaptive and personalized global collaborative information into sequential recommendation systems.

item.title: Truly Scale-Equivariant Deep Nets with Fourier Layers
item.description: In computer vision, models must be able to adapt to changes in image resolution to effectively carry out tasks such as image segmentation; This is known as scale-equivariance.

item.title: A Foundation Model for Music Informatics
item.description: This paper investigates foundation models tailored for music informatics, a domain currently challenged by the scarcity of labeled data and generalization issues.

item.title: GTP-ViT: Efficient Vision Transformers via Graph-based Token Propagation
item.description: Vision Transformers (ViTs) have revolutionized the field of computer vision, yet their deployments on resource-constrained devices remain challenging due to high computational demands.

item.title: Zero-shot Bilingual App Reviews Mining with Large Language Models
item.description: App reviews from app stores are crucial for improving software requirements.

item.title: 1D-Convolutional transformer for Parkinson disease diagnosis from gait
item.description: Our experimental results show that our approach is effective for detecting the different stages of Parkinson's disease from gait data, with a final accuracy of 88%, outperforming other state-of-the-art AI methods on the Physionet gait dataset.

item.title: A Two-Stage Generative Model with CycleGAN and Joint Diffusion for MRI-based Brain Tumor Detection
item.description: However, current supervised learning methods require extensively annotated images and the state-of-the-art generative models used in unsupervised methods often have limitations in covering the whole data distribution.

item.title: InstructPix2NeRF: Instructed 3D Portrait Editing from a Single Image
item.description: With the help of our proposed token position randomization strategy, we could even achieve multi-semantic editing through one single pass with the portrait identity well-preserved.

item.title: An Efficient Self-Supervised Cross-View Training For Sentence Embedding
item.description: In this paper, we propose a framework called Self-supervised Cross-View Training (SCT) to narrow the performance gap between large and small PLMs.
